Wineglass Ranch is a working cattle ranch in Northern Central Arizona with 100 acres of private land, home, guest cabin and 78, 000+ Acres of USFS Grazing lease. Located between Flagstaff, Prescott AZ and Las Vegas NV in the Prescott and beautiful Kaibab National Forest, this working cattle ranch is available for acquisition. It includes a quality 150 head of cattle currently on the ranch and offers the opportunity to adopt the ranching lifestyle. The Wineglass Ranch headquarters and winter pastures are north of Prescott in Paulden and the summer pastures are just west of Flagstaff, where the landscape is filled with ponderosa pines, rolling high desert grasslands and mountain views. The ranch offers and nice combination of grazing with the amazingly beautiful summer pastures north of Parks Arizona, plentiful with a wide variety of mountain meadow grasses and browse, and the mild winter grazing in the Paulden/ Chino Valley area. The ranch currently supports grazing for 237 mother cows' year long. Access between the 4 summer and winter grazing Allotments totaling over 78, 000-acre National Forest, is by I40 and Highway 89. There is a nice amount of yearly rain and light snowfall to provide natural water sources which include springs, numerous dirt tanks. The Ranch is equipped with two water wells, storage tanks, and provides continuous year-round water supply. The Well on the 10 acres private acres services a set of working corrals and provides water to pastures of the winter pastures in the Prescott National Forest. Improved infrastructure includes new WELL in March of 2025 on the USFS. Hell's Well is solar, 600' 10 gpm with storage tank. There is currently a new waterline system in place with 4 1/2 miles of pipeline. The Ranch headquarters has a new modular home, 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, has a hayshed and the guest cabin is under construction and nearly complete. The Wineglass Ranch is some of the most scenic lands in Northern Arizona!
